,Recommended,277590,23554891,"Posted: 14 June, 2016",all,Amdod,"Overall:Freedom Cry is a great DLC and I recommend it to those who both enjoy Black Flag and appreciate Adewale. If all you care about is Edward, then maybe stay away from this.What I liked:+ Adewale is a fantastic character to play as. He also seems to be perhaps the most sensible Assassin that you get to play as, having a better understanding of the Creed and how decisions should reflect it...although maybe it's just more noticeable because he's contrasted with Edward, who doesn't really get it for a very long time.+ I actually enjoyed being ""limited"" to the blunderbuss and machete as main weapons. The machete fits perfectly with Ade anyway, but the blunderbuss was a nice touch, even though I preferred the version that was better at range than spread.+ I am very glad that you are able to simply sail around to take down ships and raid plantations as in the main game, so even if the story doesn't appeal to you, you can still have an enjoyable time wreaking havoc, freeing slaves, and upgrading the Experto Crede.What I disliked:- The relative shortness of this DLC (which is understandable, so I don't count it as a negative).- Aside from finishing the storyline fairly quickly, the liberation goals seemed to be set very low. I finished those before the story was over, so now that I've finished the story, there's not much to keep me playing, aside from trying to get 100% synchronization (which isn't too difficult when you don't have to complete all of the constraints in one playthrough).- The fact that several of Ade's objectives, albeit optional, were geared toward being stealthy and/or non-violent, which I don't really feel suits his character. Especially in the setting, as a rather heavily-geared black man should stand out a lot more than someone like Edward would. While that can be used as justification for having Ade have more of a stealth emphasis, I would have liked for the game to have him just embrace that issue and put himself out there, daring people to challenge him.- No sea shanties. At all. Disappointing."
