,Recommended,277590,17860367,"Posted: 3 September, 2015",all,Little Puffski,"AC: Freedom CryShort, standalone story with simple premise, but featuring two strong characters that have some quite good conversations in between the missions and are the best thing about this DLC. Other than that, it's very similar to AC4, taking most of the features, often simplifing them, since it's on much smaller scale, and unfortunately bearing all the problems AC games have.And the bugs! Oh god, the glitches. I've never seen something like this (haven't played Unity yet) - enemies suddenly spawning from their dead comrades (and instantly raising alarm), friendly AI falling down from ladders and killing themselves, invisible enemies that appear on minimap, the good old ""I just wanted to jump over that wall, not walk on it"", just to name few that were the most memorable, but I kid you not, when this DLC breaks, it breaks hard. I do not remember having such a hard time with AC4 or any previous AC.Still, even without the bugs, the experience is very limited and other than the story, the exploration is so bare bone that it honestly isn't worth it, you won't find anything different from AC4, where pretty much everything is more fleshed out, so I can only recommend this for the story and when on sale, not for it's regular asking price.Decent, but (often) flawed experience."
