,Recommended,277590,14206463,"Posted: 28 January, 2015",all,Reminiscence,"It's very simple. If you liked Assassin's Creed IV: Black Flag, you'll like this one too. If you didn't like Black Flag, Freedom Cry probably won't change your mind.The main difference between Black Flag and Freedom Cry is its theme. Instead of being all about pirates and their shenanigans, this game is basically Django Unchained in 18th century Haiti: Your main goal is violently freeing slaves.I could go on a lengthy spiel now about what else this game involves, but frankly, there's no need for that. Who doesn't know what Assassin's Creed is by now?Because there's no ""Maybe I'll recommend this"" option for Steam Reviews, I'll just say that I would personally recommend it. I liked Black Flag, and Freedom Cry is more of the same."
